    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.51-53_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">51</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your first class is over and while my appreciation is fresh you must hear from your student.</p>
                
                <p>I see you through the clutter of children, interrupted by flashes of "boy-stuff." On television you and your words are all mine, I share you with no other classmates. You have a new advantage over old ways of teaching.</p>
                
                <p>I hope you and the University realize the privilege it is for us to share your thoughts and teaching. Mothers are supposed to "have time," but there are real difficulties in attending
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.51-53_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">52</fw>
                
                    formal classes. And mothers are people who profit from inspiration such as you give.</p>
                
                <p>Someday I hope to see you in your office &#8212; now I must make some music. <unclear>&amp;</unclear> what happens in the kitchen for it is time for supper.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mrs. Ted Fisher</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Route 1</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.51-53_0003"/>
                
